        <h1><strong>Facebook Requirments</strong></h1>
        <p> To Activate your Facebook inside the Social Hub, we need the following items:</p>
        <ul>
        <li>The App's ID</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
        <li>The App's secret Key</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
        <li>The "Slug Name" or ID of the facebook profile you would like to show</li>
        </ul>
        <br><br>
        <h1><strong>Steps</strong></h1>
        <p>Creating an application in facebook</p>
        <p>To create an application in facebook you need to go to : <a href="https://developers.facebook.com/" target="_blank">https://developers.facebook.com</a>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>


            <center> <img src="img/fb1.jpg" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <ol>
        <li><strong>Becoming a developer</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <p><em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(FYI: If you are already a Facebook developer, please skip this step.)</em></p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">For you to create a Facebook app you first need to become a Facebook developer and accept their terms and conditions</P>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>


          <center> <img src="img/fb2.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <ol start="2">
        <li><strong>Creating an APP</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;If this is your first Facebook App please click on the "Create App" button. If you already have an App, you will see a list of your apps and a button to create a new one called "Create a new App" </p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>


            <center> <img src="img/fb3.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p style="padding-left: 300px;">&nbsp;</p>


                  <center> <img src="img/fb4.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p style="padding-left: 300px;">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">Define your App name as <em>GotChosen</em> <em>APP</em>, input an email for contact and also choose a caterogry that best fits you, and click "Save".</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>


                    <center> <img src="img/fb5.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p style="padding-left: 300px;">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">After you will need to click on Settings -> basic to access application detail modal</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>


                    <center> <img src="img/fb6.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p style="padding-left: 300px;">&nbsp;</p>
        <ol start="3">
        <li><strong>Defining your Application domain</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">Inside the App Domains field add <em>gotchosen</em><em>.com</em>. This will give GotChosen Permisson</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 90px;">- GotChosen can now access Facebook's API to obtain information</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>


                    <center> <img src="img/fb7.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <ol start="4">
        <li><strong>Adding a platform</strong></li>
        </ol>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">After defining the App domain, click on <strong>"Add</strong> <strong>platform"</strong>.</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>


                  <center> <img src="img/fb8.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>

        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">Select <strong>"Site"</strong> as your platform <strong>.</strong></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>


                    <center> <img src="img/fb9.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">Inside the URL field type <em>https://gotchosen</em><em>.com</em><strong>.</strong></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>


                    <center> <img src="img/fb10.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">Now we can save all our changes by just clicking on the "Save Changes" button on the lower right side of the page.</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>


                  <center> <img src="img/fb11.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>

        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>5. identifying your "Slug Name" or ID </p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">To identify your <strong>"Slug</strong> <strong>Name"</strong> is very simple, all you have to do is access your Facebook page, and your "Slug Name" will be in the URL</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>


                  <center> <img src="img/fb12.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">If your URL does not contain your "Slug Name" it will be a sequence of numbers which is your ID (FYI:The ID could also contain your facebook's channel name not just numbers) </p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>


                  <center> <img src="img/fb13.png" alt="" style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px" > </center>


        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="padding-left: 60px;">&nbsp;</p>





